    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="796"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d796">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-11T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2182. Your 2866. The Department considers that the Government of the United
                    States is as much concerned in cases where the lives of American citizens are
                    endangered as it is in cases where there has been a loss of American lives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
